iltration. On one hand, it is compact, but on the other hand, it lacks any standout features. It uses a three-stage purification system, but without its ionizer, it loses much of its filtration power. So much of the Hunter PermaLife works, but not well enough to impress.","The Hunter PermaLife uses a three-stage filtration system, designed to reduce allergens and odors in small rooms. First, the carbon prefilter catches large particles and odors. This filter has an effective life of three months. Next, the PermaLife Filter traps smaller pollutants such as dust and pollen. This HEPA-grade filter works for six months. Finally, the optional ionizer electromagnetically charges outgoing particles. This makes them easier to catch on the second pass.","However, the Hunter&#39;s ionizer does generate ozone while in operation, and studies show that charged particles can damage healthy lungs. If you have sensitive lungs, we&#39;d like to recommend turning off the ionizer to eliminate ozone production, but when we contacted Hunter, none of the representatives we spoke with knew whether the PermaLife Filter is ozone free.","The Hunter PermaLife lacks many of the convenience features we look for. It does not have an operation scheduler or timer to control the amount of ions you are using. Also, it does not use an air-quality sensor to monitor indoor pollution and filter performance. Instead of a traditional filter monitor, it features a calendar. Three- and six-month dials spin on the control panel, and whenever you change one of the filters, you have to adjust the dial to let you know the next time the filter needs to be changed. While it does have a filter monitor, it hardly makes the Hunter PermaLife easier to use or more convenient.","The best thing about the PermaLife is its five-year warranty. Hunter&#39;s website has a FAQs section and downloadable user manuals. If you need more help, customer support representatives are available by phone and email."]},"id":"e79bc6b6-41ae-4491-8a6f-167b4abd4bae","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"42d06c0d-d526-4611-b550-473d3aa78505","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The Hunter PermaLife is a compact tower air purifier that is good for small rooms. Its triple-purifying system offers middling performance, though, and you&#39;ll have to use the optional ionizer for best filtration. The Hunter PermaLife lacks any convenience features that would make it stand out."]},"id":"dc193198-7bfb-490f-b640-6ec43876b800","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_56452","url":"/hunter-permalife-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"john-carlsen","url":"/author/john-carlsen","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"John Carlsen","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"jN6fuw55cS2xYQi25mfgkg","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2013-05-20T21:56:06Z","datePublished":"2013-05-20T21:56:06Z","name":"Hunter PermaLife","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been discontinued. You can still read our original review below, but Top Ten Reviews is no longer updating this product’s information.","review":{"rating":43,"verdict":"The Hunter PermaLife is good for small rooms, but this tower air purifier lacks any features to make it stand out.","pros":["The Hunter PermaLife is thin and takes up very little space."],"cons":["For full purification capabilities, you&#039;ll have to use the optional ionizer."]},"strapline":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been discontinued. You can still read our original review below, but Top Ten Reviews is no longer updating this product’s information.","language":"en","dateModified":"2013-05-20T21:56:06Z","id":"LjcrbowV4D2gooGfctMXJ6","meta":{"title":"Hunter PermaLife Review - Pros, Cons and Verdict","description":"Tower air purifiers like the Hunter PermaLife 